IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT
FOR THE DISTRICT OF DELAWARE
CARD CONNECT, LLC,
Plaintiff,
V.
C.A. No. 19-2082-CFC-CJB
SHIFT4 PAYMENTS, LLC, et al., :
Defendants.
ORDER
At Wilmington this Seventh day of June in 2021, consistent with the Report and
Recommendation issued this same day,
IT IS HEREBY ORDERED that:
1. Shift4's Motion for Sanctions Pursuant to Rule 37(c)(l) and the Court's Inherent
Authority (D.I. 278) is GRANTED-IN-PART AND DENIED-IN-PART.
Specifically:
(a) The Motion is GRANTED in that Defendants are precluded from
calling Mr. R***** as a witness at trial and they also may not use
any documents authored by Mr. R***** that were, disclosed for
the first time in January 2021 or thereafter for substantive
purposes at trial; but
(b) In all other respects, the Motion is DENIED; and that:
2. Shift4==s Motion for Sanctions Pursuant to 28 U.S.C. 1927 (D.I. 284) is DENIED.
